Busia Governor Sospeter Ojaamong (pictiured) has linked the water shortage in Teso North to sabotage from those in charge of distributing the commodity. He said he toured the Malakisi water treatment plant to find out why supply to Teso North was cut off.&ldquo;Why are residents of Malakisi division receiving water from the same treatment plant if there is no foul play?&rdquo; Ojaamong asked on Sunday.He said he will camp in the area to ensure water supply to Amagoro and Malaba is restored. But Water executive Gregory Odeke said the shortage was caused by vandalism.